{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 132, "line_start": 132, "page_hint": null, "section": "Kno3", "text": "For the fluorides, molar volumes obtained from the density measurements agreed within $2\\%$ with volumes calculated from additive contributions of the components."}
{"claim_type": "salt-chemistry", "line_end": 132, "line_start": 132, "page_hint": null, "section": "Kno3", "text": "The expansivities of three LiF-BeF $_2$ -ThF $_4$ mixtures were practically identical, $2.5 \\times 10^{-4} / ^{\\circ}\\mathrm{C}$ ."}
{"claim_type": "salt-chemistry", "line_end": 134, "line_start": 134, "page_hint": null, "section": "Kno3", "text": "Density-temperature curves from $25 - 700^{\\circ}\\mathrm{C}$ for $\\mathrm{LiF - BeF_2 - ThF_4}$ (72-16-12 mole %) and for $\\mathrm{NaBF_4 - NaF}$ (92-8 mole %) were derived from room-temperature pycnometric determinations and from estimated expansivities of the solid salts."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 134, "line_start": 134, "page_hint": null, "section": "Kno3", "text": "The calculated expansion, upon melting, for the former is $7\\%$ , for the latter $8\\%$ ."}
{"claim_type": "salt-chemistry", "line_end": 139, "line_start": 139, "page_hint": null, "section": "Kno3", "text": "LiF-BeF2-ThF4 (72.7-15.7-11.6, 70.1-23.9-6.0 mole %) NaBF4-NaF (92-8 mole %)"}
{"claim_type": "figure-reference", "line_end": 150, "line_start": 150, "page_hint": null, "section": "Experimental", "text": "Apparatus and Procedures: Densities were determined in a nickel dilatometer (Figure 1), the details of which have been previously described. $^{1,2}$ In the apparatus a metal probe detects the changes in liquid level in the neck of a volume-calibrated metal vessel."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 150, "line_start": 150, "page_hint": null, "section": "Experimental", "text": "The probe height is measured to $\\pm 0.02$ mm with a cathetometer."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 150, "line_start": 150, "page_hint": null, "section": "Experimental", "text": "By taking measurements at argon pressures of approximately 5 atm, entrapped gas bubble volumes were reduced to less than $0.1\\%$ of the liquid sample."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 154, "line_start": 154, "page_hint": null, "section": "Experimental", "text": "Melt temperatures were controlled to $\\pm 0.2^{\\circ}$ by regulating the furnace with a Leeds and Northrup Speedomax proportional controller."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 154, "line_start": 154, "page_hint": null, "section": "Experimental", "text": "Temperatures of the melt were determined with Pt-Rh thermocouples previously calibrated by the National Bureau of Standards; these thermocouples are stated to be accurate within $0.5^{\\circ}$ in the temperature range $(400 - 820^{\\circ}\\mathrm{C})$ of measurement."}
{"claim_type": "salt-chemistry", "line_end": 161, "line_start": 161, "page_hint": null, "section": "Materials", "text": "The salt mixtures, $\\mathrm{LiF - BeF_2}$ (66-34 mole %) and $\\mathrm{LiF - BeF_2 - ZrF_4}$ (64.7-30.1-5.2 mole %), were supplied by J."}
{"claim_type": "salt-chemistry", "line_end": 161, "line_start": 161, "page_hint": null, "section": "Materials", "text": "Shaffer, ORNL, from batches that had been sparged by $\\mathrm{H}_2$ -HF gaseous treatment.<sup>3</sup> By adding purified, crystalline LiF and $\\mathrm{UF_4}$ to the latter, we prepared $\\mathrm{LiF - BeF_2 - ZrF_4 - UF_4}$ (64.79-29.96-4.99-0.26 mole %)."}
{"claim_type": "salt-chemistry", "line_end": 163, "line_start": 163, "page_hint": null, "section": "Materials", "text": "Mixtures of LiF-BeF $_2$ -ThF $_4$ (used in both density and viscosity measurements) were constituted from LiF-BeF $_2$ (66-34 mole %), crystalline LiF, and LiF-ThF $_4$ mixtures."}
{"claim_type": "salt-chemistry", "line_end": 163, "line_start": 163, "page_hint": null, "section": "Materials", "text": "The mixture, NaBF $_4$ -NaF (92-8 mole %), was constituted from the purified components. $^{2,6}$"}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 167, "line_start": 167, "page_hint": null, "section": "Materials", "text": "The gas was shown by mass spectrographic analysis to exceed $99.9\\%$ in purity."}
{"claim_type": "figure-reference", "line_end": 169, "line_start": 169, "page_hint": null, "section": "Materials", "text": "To insure that the liquid level reached into the neck of the vessel (see Figure 1), two loadings were usually required; after melting the initial charge of the salt, the vessel was returned to the glovebox for further loading."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 173, "line_start": 173, "page_hint": null, "section": "Results", "text": "The densities of seven fluoride mixtures were measured over about a $200^{\\circ}\\mathrm{C}$ temperature range."}
{"claim_type": "table-reference", "line_end": 173, "line_start": 173, "page_hint": null, "section": "Results", "text": "Data for $\\mathrm{KNO}_3$ are given in Table 2."}
